WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:13.280
Hi, I am Danielle Oberdier, the founder of dikayodata.com, a data science media company

00:00:13.280 --> 00:00:15.960
and the DataFem podcast.

00:00:15.960 --> 00:00:23.040
And I'm here to talk to you about how content makes our industry go round and stay connected

00:00:23.040 --> 00:00:24.639
to one another.

00:00:24.639 --> 00:00:29.799
So if you have more questions, because this is a lightning talk, please reach out on Twitter

00:00:29.799 --> 00:00:37.160
at dikayodata or at my site, dikayodata.com, I'm always happy to talk and clarify more

00:00:37.160 --> 00:00:42.840
things that I don't get to this time.

00:00:42.840 --> 00:00:44.360
So what to make?

00:00:44.360 --> 00:00:50.320
There are several types of content that you can make when you're starting out making content.

00:00:50.320 --> 00:00:56.680
One obviously is an audio podcast, but that takes a ton of time editing, finding guests,

00:00:56.680 --> 00:01:02.919
finding sponsors, and it's a lot of work, whereas a blog is only the amount of work

00:01:02.919 --> 00:01:04.320
that you want to make it.

00:01:04.320 --> 00:01:09.180
You can be amazing like Julia Siljan, do YouTube tutorials, but that is not something within

00:01:09.180 --> 00:01:10.639
my expertise.

00:01:10.639 --> 00:01:16.639
I do blog, I love it, I love making tutorials that people can just look at really quickly

00:01:16.639 --> 00:01:20.239
without turning off their TV shows and just get right to the point.

00:01:20.239 --> 00:01:26.800
I love writing about general trends, career trends in the industry.

00:01:26.800 --> 00:01:33.839
What's interesting is that long form content is totally in, average of 1,200 words is what

00:01:33.839 --> 00:01:35.279
is the most popular.

00:01:35.279 --> 00:01:40.279
So if you want to just write content every month, every two months, and you have something

00:01:40.279 --> 00:01:45.279
to say, know that that long form piece is going to be something that people are interested

00:01:45.279 --> 00:01:46.919
in.

00:01:46.919 --> 00:01:52.519
In terms of where to share, that's where I just want to give a shout out to email marketing.

00:01:52.519 --> 00:01:54.519
Email marketing is very important.

00:01:54.519 --> 00:02:04.639
Nine out of 10 marketers still use email to promote their products, and 81% of small businesses

00:02:04.639 --> 00:02:08.800
use email as the primary way of connecting with their customers.

00:02:08.800 --> 00:02:13.399
So I do have an email list, I suggest that if you have a product that you really want

00:02:13.399 --> 00:02:17.919
to circulate to your audience, definitely set up on email.

00:02:17.919 --> 00:02:22.119
There are so many ways to set up an email list with your blog.

00:02:22.119 --> 00:02:28.039
I recommend Squarespace, and I am always available to talk about this, like I said.

00:02:28.039 --> 00:02:29.559
Who it helps.

00:02:29.559 --> 00:02:35.880
Obviously, having content in our industry really helps bring new talent into the fold.

00:02:35.880 --> 00:02:42.559
You can't just expect to post on LinkedIn and have all the right people get to your

00:02:42.720 --> 00:02:43.720
message.

00:02:43.720 --> 00:02:48.199
You do have to write content that is targeted towards people that might not feel comfortable

00:02:48.199 --> 00:02:50.800
addressing certain issues in the industry.

00:02:50.800 --> 00:02:59.080
Talk to them, bring them in, definitely think about what kind of content you're addressing,

00:02:59.080 --> 00:03:06.360
think about current events, and it obviously helps newcomers.

00:03:06.360 --> 00:03:10.839
It also helps all of us who might not be newcomers to the field.

00:03:10.839 --> 00:03:11.839
Why it matters.

00:03:12.360 --> 00:03:17.440
A lot of us don't think about talking more about content after our work is over with

00:03:17.440 --> 00:03:24.399
just the few packages that we've been working with all day that our projects tend to use.

00:03:24.399 --> 00:03:29.839
If we want to think outside the box and relate to each other, then the content that we circulate

00:03:29.839 --> 00:03:33.199
really fosters that discussion outside of the workplace.

00:03:33.199 --> 00:03:40.360
I think it gives those of us that are in higher positions a way to connect with other people

00:03:40.360 --> 00:03:44.440
in other industries who are doing really good things that they didn't know about.

00:03:44.440 --> 00:03:49.039
I know that Datafem is often a connector for people who never would have met but listened

00:03:49.039 --> 00:03:56.240
to the same podcast and then end up having a discussion maybe on social media.

00:03:56.240 --> 00:04:00.240
And here we finally get to how to succeed.

00:04:00.240 --> 00:04:03.720
Consistency is really important, but you can set the barometer for that.

00:04:03.720 --> 00:04:07.600
You do not have to say that consistency means every day.

00:04:07.600 --> 00:04:09.240
It could mean once a month.

00:04:09.240 --> 00:04:13.320
It could even mean once a year for certain projects.

00:04:13.320 --> 00:04:17.959
Really what matters is that you're consistent about how you promote your content.

00:04:17.959 --> 00:04:22.359
You're consistent in having discussions in person at work on social media.

00:04:22.359 --> 00:04:27.679
That really matters because that is really the most important of your content's life

00:04:27.679 --> 00:04:30.920
story is who it reaches and how.

00:04:30.920 --> 00:04:35.760
So you can make the best content in the world, but if it never reaches anybody, you're not

00:04:35.760 --> 00:04:42.480
going to really succeed in the way that the industry could benefit from.

00:04:42.480 --> 00:04:50.720
So definitely no matter how much you write or record, make sure that you're always having

00:04:50.720 --> 00:04:56.160
conversations to help you grow, your content grow, and the industry grow.

00:04:56.160 --> 00:04:57.239
Thank you so much.

